dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Tarnow, sheet T-15 A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 1. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Tarnow, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 and Danube zone grids. Relief shown by 20 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Poland 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 48-31, 1938; 48-32, 1937; 49-31, 1937 and 49-32, 1937. Road classification based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
